              <span id="reviewTextContainer4357699620" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10978300761684947092"><strong>Incredibly honest</strong><br/><br/>“The forever war“ is a book that is sometimes difficult to reach because of the cost of pain and murderous actions of war. In my opinion I see it as a war that was fought by politicians but using the soldiers as their pawns.<br/><br/>And it reads very smoothly and it reads very quickly. The descriptions are precise, even though the preciseness causes one to cringe.<br/><br/>If you were the one who is the history or your Pham, then I recommend this book to you.<br/><br/></span>

          </span>
