<div id="review_3765822348" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3765822348" />
    <a title="Leftbanker" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/352711-leftbanker"><img alt="Leftbanker" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1530584670p2/352711.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3765822348?book_show_action=true">Jan 16, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Leftbanker" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Leftbanker" href="/user/show/352711-leftbanker">Leftbanker</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/352711-leftbanker?shelf=war">war</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/352711-leftbanker?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/352711-leftbanker?shelf=politics">politics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3765822348" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6140683690841718063">If you are looking for a history of the Iraq War, you need to look elsewhere. This is more a collection of stories and musings from one of the great reporters of our time on conflicts we should have never entered into and are still mired in almost twenty years later. This is a subject that I followed intimately while it was happening, reading everything worth reading on the topic while also having been informed by my own years as a student of Arabic and Middle East politics.<br/><br/>As we see the afterma</span>
  <span id="freeText6140683690841718063" style="display:none">If you are looking for a history of the Iraq War, you need to look elsewhere. This is more a collection of stories and musings from one of the great reporters of our time on conflicts we should have never entered into and are still mired in almost twenty years later. This is a subject that I followed intimately while it was happening, reading everything worth reading on the topic while also having been informed by my own years as a student of Arabic and Middle East politics.<br /><br />As we see the aftermath of yet another disastrous Republican administration, we can’t forget about the shitshow brought to us by the last Republican in the White House. I know that I haven’t forgotten, and I’ve been doing a serious review of the matter as of late.<br /><br />What Filkins harps on again and again was the complete savagery of this war, from top to bottom, something predicted by anyone and everyone familiar with this area before we invaded. I remember sitting in one of my favorite martini bar in Seattle on the eve of the Iraq invasion, probably in February of 2003. The group sitting next to me were screaming for revenge over the 9/11 attacks and how the U.S. needed to attack Iraq and give us some sort of payback. I leaned over and asked them if they knew the difference between Sunni and Shia Muslims. Of course, they didn’t. I told them that they’d find out soon enough.<br /><br />Once again, we see the complete failure of our military elites in the USA. As the old saying goes, if you are a hammer, everything looks like a nail. Our military leaders can never seem to get it through their thick skulls that most of the problems in the world can't be solved with violence. In fact, violence only serves to exacerbate the issues being addressed. The generals learned nothing from our total failures in Viet Nam, Afghanistan, and Iraq. Where will be the next catastrophic error in U.S. foreign policy when we allow the Pentagon to lead the way? </span>
  <a data-text-id="6140683690841718063" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

